    },
    {
      "content": "Introduces batch and high performance computing (Big Compute) scenarios and solution options in Azure",
      "pos": [
        98,
        199
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Batch and HPC Solutions",
      "pos": [
        507,
        530
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "This article introduces Azure solutions for batch and high performance computing (HPC) - also called <bpt id=\"p1\">*</bpt>Big Compute<ept id=\"p1\">*</ept>.",
      "pos": [
        532,
        647
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Although the article is mainly for technical decision-makers, IT managers, and independent software vendors, other IT professionals and developers can use it to familiarize themselves with these solutions.",
      "pos": [
        648,
        853
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Organizations have large-scale computing problems including engineering design and analysis, image rendering, complex modeling, Monte Carlo simulations, and financial risk calculations.",
      "pos": [
        855,
        1040
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "To help organizations solve these problems and make decisions with the resources, scale, and schedule they need, Azure offers scalable, on-demand compute capabilities and services.",
      "pos": [
        1041,
        1221
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "With Azure, organizations can:",
      "pos": [
        1222,
        1252
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Create hybrid solutions, extending an on-premises HPC cluster to offload peak workloads to the cloud",
      "pos": [
        1256,
        1356
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Run HPC cluster workloads entirely in Azure using existing tool sets and applications",
      "pos": [
        1360,
        1445
      ]
    },
    {
      "pos": [
        1449,
        1657
      ],
      "content": "Use a managed and scalable Azure service such as <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>Batch<ept id=\"p1\">](http://azure.microsoft.com/documentation/services/batch/)</ept> to run compute-intensive workloads without having to deploy and manage compute infrastructure"
    },
    {
      "content": "Azure also offers development tools and services for organizations and software vendors to build custom, end-to-end Big Compute solutions.",
      "pos": [
        1659,
        1797
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Background: Batch and HPC applications",
      "pos": [
        1803,
        1841
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Unlike web applications and many line-of-business applications, batch and HPC applications have a defined beginning and end, and they can run on a schedule or on demand, sometimes for hours or longer.",
      "pos": [
        1843,
        2043
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Most fall into two main categories: <bpt id=\"p1\">*</bpt>intrinsically parallel<ept id=\"p1\">*</ept> (sometimes called “embarrassingly parallel”, because the problems they solve lend themselves to running in parallel on multiple computers or processors) and <bpt id=\"p2\">*</bpt>tightly coupled<ept id=\"p2\">*</ept>.",
      "pos": [
        2044,
        2280
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "See the following table for more about these application types.",
      "pos": [
        2281,
        2344
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Some Azure solution approaches work better for one type or the other.",
      "pos": [
        2345,
        2414
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "<ph id=\"ph1\">[AZURE.NOTE]</ph> In Batch and HPC solutions, a running instance of an application is typically called a <bpt id=\"p1\">*</bpt>job<ept id=\"p1\">*</ept>, and each job might get divided into <bpt id=\"p2\">*</bpt>tasks<ept id=\"p2\">*</ept>.",
      "pos": [
        2417,
        2568
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "And the clustered compute resources for the application are often called <bpt id=\"p1\">*</bpt>compute nodes<ept id=\"p1\">*</ept>.",
      "pos": [
        2569,
        2658
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Type",
      "pos": [
        2660,
        2664
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Characteristics",
      "pos": [
        2667,
        2682
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Examples",
      "pos": [
        2685,
        2693
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "<bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Intrinsically parallel<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept>",
      "pos": [
        2740,
        2766
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "![Intrinsically parallel][parallel]",
      "pos": [
        2776,
        2811
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "• Individual computers run application logic independently",
      "pos": [
        2813,
        2871
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "• Adding computers allows the application to scale and decrease computation time",
      "pos": [
        2882,
        2962
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "• Application consists of separate executables, or is divided into a group of services invoked by a client (a service-oriented architecture, or SOA, application)",
      "pos": [
        2972,
        3133
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "• Financial risk modeling",
      "pos": [
        3135,
        3160
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "• Image rendering and image processing",
      "pos": [
        3170,
        3208
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "• Media encoding and transcoding",
      "pos": [
        3218,
        3250
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "• Monte Carlo simulations",
      "pos": [
        3260,
        3285
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "• Software testing",
      "pos": [
        3295,
        3313
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "<bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Tightly coupled<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept>",
      "pos": [
        3314,
        3333
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "![Tightly coupled][coupled]",
      "pos": [
        3343,
        3370
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "• Application requires compute nodes to interact or exchange intermediate results",
      "pos": [
        3372,
        3453
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "• Compute nodes may communicate using the Message Passing Interface (MPI), a common communications protocol for parallel computing",
      "pos": [
        3463,
        3593
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "• The application is sensitive to network latency and bandwidth",
      "pos": [
        3603,
        3666
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "• Application performance can be improved by using compute infrastructure that supports high-speed networking technologies such as InfiniBand and remote direct memory access (RDMA)",
      "pos": [
        3676,
        3856
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "• Oil and gas reservoir modeling",
      "pos": [
        3858,
        3890
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "• Engineering design and analysis, such as computational fluid dynamics",
      "pos": [
        3900,
        3971
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "• Physical simulations such as car crashes and nuclear reactions",
      "pos": [
        3981,
        4045
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "• Weather forecasting",
      "pos": [
        4055,
        4076
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Considerations for running batch and HPC applications in the cloud",
      "pos": [
        4082,
        4148
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "You can readily migrate many applications that are designed to run in on-premises HPC clusters to Azure, or to a hybrid (cross-premises) environment.",
      "pos": [
        4150,
        4299
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "However, there may be some limitations or considerations, including:",
      "pos": [
        4300,
        4368
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "<bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Uninterrupted availability of cloud resources<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> - Depending on the type of cloud compute resources selected for the solution, you might not be able to rely on continuous machine availability for the duration of a job's execution.",
      "pos": [
        4373,
        4604
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "State handling and progress check pointing are common techniques to handle possible transient failures, and more necessary when leveraging cloud resources.",
      "pos": [
        4605,
        4760
      ]
    },
    {
      "pos": [
        4765,
        5010
      ],
      "content": "<bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Data access<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> - Data access techniques commonly available within an enterprise network cluster, such as NFS, may require special configuration in the cloud, or you might need to adopt different data access practices and patterns for the cloud."
    },
    {
      "content": "<bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Data movement<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> - For applications that process large amounts of data, strategies are needed to move the data into cloud storage and to compute resources, and you might need to consider high-speed cross-premises networking such as <bpt id=\"p2\">[</bpt>Azure ExpressRoute<ept id=\"p2\">](http://azure.microsoft.com/services/expressroute/)</ept>.",
      "pos": [
        5014,
        5319
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Also consider legal, regulatory, or policy limitations for storing or accessing that data.",
      "pos": [
        5320,
        5410
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "<bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Licensing<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> - Check with the vendor of any commercial application for licensing or other restrictions for running in the cloud.",
      "pos": [
        5415,
        5544
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Not all vendors offer pay-as-you-go licensing.",
      "pos": [
        5545,
        5591
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "You might need to plan for a licensing server in the cloud for your solution, or a connection to an on-premises license server.",
      "pos": [
        5592,
        5719
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Big Compute or Big Data?",
      "pos": [
        5726,
        5750
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "The dividing lines between Big Compute and Big Data applications aren’t always clear, and some applications may have characteristics of both.",
      "pos": [
        5752,
        5893
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Both involve running large-scale computations, usually on clusters of computers that run on-premises, in the cloud, or both.",
      "pos": [
        5894,
        6018
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "But the solution approaches and supporting tools might differ.",
      "pos": [
        6019,
        6081
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "• <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Big Compute<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> tends to involve applications that rely on CPU power and memory, such as engineering simulations, financial risk modeling, and digital rendering.",
      "pos": [
        6083,
        6246
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "The clusters that power a Big Compute solution might include computers with specialized multicore processors to perform raw computation, and specialized, high speed networking hardware to connect the computers.",
      "pos": [
        6247,
        6457
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "• <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Big Data<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> solves data analysis problems that involve large amounts of data that can’t be managed by a single computer or database management system, such as large volumes of web logs or other business intelligence data.",
      "pos": [
        6459,
        6683
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Big Data tends to rely more on disk capacity and I/O performance than on CPU power, and a Big Data solution often uses specialized tools such as Apache Hadoop to manage the cluster and partition the data.",
      "pos": [
        6684,
        6888
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "(For information about Azure HDInsight and other Azure Hadoop solutions, see <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>Hadoop<ept id=\"p1\">](http://azure.microsoft.com/solutions/hadoop/)</ept>.)",
      "pos": [
        6889,
        7022
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Resource management and job scheduling",
      "pos": [
        7027,
        7065
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Running Batch and HPC application usually includes a <bpt id=\"p1\">*</bpt>cluster manager<ept id=\"p1\">*</ept> and a <bpt id=\"p2\">*</bpt>job scheduler<ept id=\"p2\">*</ept> to help manage clustered compute resources and allocate them to the applications that run the jobs.",
      "pos": [
        7067,
        7259
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "These functions might be accomplished by separate tools, or an integrated tool.",
      "pos": [
        7260,
        7339
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "<bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Cluster manager<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> - Provisions, releases, and administers compute resources (or compute nodes).",
      "pos": [
        7343,
        7440
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Depending on the tool, a cluster manager might automate installation of operating system images and applications on compute nodes, scale compute resources according to demands, and monitor the performance of the nodes.",
      "pos": [
        7441,
        7659
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "<bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Job scheduler<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> - Specifies the resources (such as processors or memory) an application needs, and the conditions when it will run.",
      "pos": [
        7663,
        7796
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "A job scheduler maintains a queue of jobs and allocates resources to them based on an assigned priority or other characteristics.",
      "pos": [
        7797,
        7926
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Clustering and job scheduling tools for Windows-based and Linux-based clusters, or those developed independently, can migrate well to Azure.",
      "pos": [
        7928,
        8068
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "For example, <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>Microsoft HPC Pack<ept id=\"p1\">](https://technet.microsoft.com/library/cc514029)</ept> is Microsoft’s free compute cluster solution for Windows Server and Windows-based computers.",
      "pos": [
        8069,
        8243
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "To reduce the need for dedicated on-premises compute resources, you can extend an HPC Pack cluster to use Azure compute nodes on demand, or deploy a cluster entirely in Azure virtual machines.",
      "pos": [
        8244,
        8436
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Big Compute workflows",
      "pos": [
        8442,
        8463
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Cluster management and job scheduling tools help accomplish a Big Compute workflow with predictable steps.",
      "pos": [
        8465,
        8571
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Depending on the solution, you might omit some steps in the following list or introduce additional, custom tools.",
      "pos": [
        8572,
        8685
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Data intensive workflows might involve additional data pre- and post-processing steps (not listed).",
      "pos": [
        8686,
        8785
      ]
    },
    {
      "pos": [
        8790,
        8923
      ],
      "content": "<bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Provision<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> - Prepare the compute environment with the necessary infrastructure, compute resources, and storage to run applications"
    },
    {
      "pos": [
        8928,
        9001
      ],
      "content": "<bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Stage<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> - Move input data and applications into the compute environment"
    },
    {
      "pos": [
        9006,
        9113
      ],
      "content": "<bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Schedule<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> - Configure jobs and tasks and allocate compute resources to them when resources are available"
    },
    {
      "pos": [
        9118,
        9215
      ],
      "content": "<bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Monitor<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> - Provide status information about job and task progress; handle errors or exceptions"
    },
    {
      "pos": [
        9220,
        9286
      ],
      "content": "<bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Finish<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> - Return results and post-process output data if needed"
    },
    {
      "content": "Azure services for Big Compute",
      "pos": [
        9291,
        9321
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Azure has a range of compute, data, networking and related services you can use for Big Compute solutions and workflows.",
      "pos": [
        9323,
        9443
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "For in-depth guidance on each of these services, see the Azure services documentation.",
      "pos": [
        9444,
        9530
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "See <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>Solution scenarios<ept id=\"p1\">](#solution-scenarios)</ept> in this article for some common approaches with Batch and HPC applications.",
      "pos": [
        9531,
        9652
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "<ph id=\"ph1\">[AZURE.NOTE]</ph> New services are regularly introduced to the Azure platform and could be useful for your scenario.",
      "pos": [
        9655,
        9766
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Use of Preview services is recommended only for test or proof of concept deployments, not production workloads.",
      "pos": [
        9767,
        9878
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "If you have questions, contact an <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>Azure partner<ept id=\"p1\">](https://pinpoint.microsoft.com/en-US/search?keyword=azure)</ept> or email <bpt id=\"p2\">*</bpt>bigcompute@microsoft.com<ept id=\"p2\">*</ept>.",
      "pos": [
        9879,
        10024
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Compute services",
      "pos": [
        10030,
        10046
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Compute services in Azure are at the core of a Big Compute solution.",
      "pos": [
        10048,
        10116
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "The compute services in the following table are used frequently and offer advantages for different scenarios.",
      "pos": [
        10117,
        10226
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "At a basic level, these services offer different modes for applications to run on virtual machine-based compute instances that Azure provides using Windows Server Hyper-V technology.",
      "pos": [
        10227,
        10409
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Depending on the service, these instances can run a variety of standard and custom Linux and Windows operating systems and tools.",
      "pos": [
        10410,
        10539
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Azure provides a <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>range of instance sizes<ept id=\"p1\">](../virtual-machines/virtual-machines-sizes-specs.md)</ept> with different configurations of CPU cores, memory, disk capacity, and other characteristics.",
      "pos": [
        10540,
        10729
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Depending on your needs you can scale the instances to thousands of cores and then scale down when you need fewer resources.",
      "pos": [
        10730,
        10854
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "<ph id=\"ph1\">[AZURE.NOTE]</ph> You can take advantage of the A8-A11 instances to improve the performance of some compute-intensive workloads, including parallel MPI applications that require a low latency and high throughput application network.",
      "pos": [
        10857,
        11084
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "See <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>About the A8, A9, A10, and A11 Compute Intensive Instances<ept id=\"p1\">](../virtual-machines/virtual-machines-a8-a9-a10-a11-specs.md)</ept>.",
      "pos": [
        11085,
        11211
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Service",
      "pos": [
        11215,
        11222
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Description",
      "pos": [
        11225,
        11236
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "<bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt><bpt id=\"p2\">[</bpt>Cloud services<ept id=\"p2\">](http://azure.microsoft.com/documentation/services/cloud-services)</ept><ept id=\"p1\">**</ept>",
      "pos": [
        11265,
        11351
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "• Can run Big Compute applications in worker role instances, which are virtual machines running a version of Windows Server and are managed entirely by Azure",
      "pos": [
        11363,
        11520
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "• Enable scalable, reliable applications with low administrative overhead, running in a platform as a service (PaaS) model",
      "pos": [
        11530,
        11652
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "• May require additional tools or development to integrate with on-premises HPC cluster solutions",
      "pos": [
        11662,
        11759
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "<bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt><bpt id=\"p2\">[</bpt>Virtual machines<ept id=\"p2\">](http://azure.microsoft.com/documentation/services/virtual-machines)</ept><ept id=\"p1\">**</ept>",
      "pos": [
        11760,
        11850
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "• Provide compute infrastructure as a service (IaaS) using Microsoft Hyper-V technology",
      "pos": [
        11862,
        11949
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "• Enable you to flexibly provision and manage persistent cloud computers from standard Windows Server or Linux images, or images and data disks you supply or from the <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>Azure Marketplace<ept id=\"p1\">](https://azure.microsoft.com/marketplace/)</ept>",
      "pos": [
        11959,
        12187
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "• Run on-premises compute cluster tools and applications entirely in the cloud",
      "pos": [
        12197,
        12275
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "<bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt><bpt id=\"p2\">[</bpt>Batch<ept id=\"p2\">](http://azure.microsoft.com/documentation/services/batch)</ept><ept id=\"p1\">**</ept>",
      "pos": [
        12276,
        12344
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "• Runs large-scale parallel and batch workloads such as image rendering and media encoding and transcoding in a fully managed service",
      "pos": [
        12356,
        12489
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "• Provides job scheduling and autoscaling of a managed pool of virtual machines",
      "pos": [
        12499,
        12578
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "• Allows developers to build and run applications as a service or cloud-enable existing applications",
      "pos": [
